Here's how your code should look:

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

The `Main` method in the `Program` class must have the signature `static void Main(string[] args)`. This is the entry point of a C# console application. The `args` parameter is an array of strings that represent the command-line arguments. In this case, we're not using any command-line arguments, so we can simply pass an empty array.

Please note that the class must be named `Program`, and it must be inside a namespace. In this case, we're using the default namespace, so we don't need any `namespace` declaration.

